      $d D x y $.
      $( Every Pell equation has a nontrivial solution.  Theorem 62 in
         [vandenDries] p. 43.  (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 19-Oct-2014.) $)
      pellex $p |- ( ( D e. NN /\ -. ( sqr ` D ) e. QQ ) -> E. x e. NN E. y e.
          NN ( ( x ^ 2 ) - ( D x. ( y ^ 2 ) ) ) = 1 ) $=
